author: M T
Shiva Kumar
text:
One more feared drowned, two rescued; rescue operations on

An evening outing ended in a tragedy for a group of residential interns (house surgeons) of the Mandya Institute of Medical Sciences (MIMS), with two of them drowning while another was feared dead in the Visvesvaraya Canal, near Keregodu in the taluk, on Friday.

The dead have been identified as Jeevan and Shruthi, residents of Bengaluru. Girish of Tumakuru is feared drowned. The local residents rescued Gowtham Patel and Sindhu.They are residents of Vijayanagar, Mysuru.
title: Two medicos drown
